Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy for Trimry
Last Updated: [2023-10-13]
Welcome to Trimry. Your privacy is of utmost importance to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, protect, and disclose your personal information when you use Trimry. Please read this policy carefully, and if you have any questions, feel free to contact us at support@trimry.com.
2. Information We Collect
When you use Trimry, we collect the following types of information:
Personal Identification Information: This includes your first name, last name, and email address.
User-Generated Content: This encompasses questions, answers, scores, games created, uploaded media, and uploaded text.
User Interactions: This covers social relations (follow, request to follow), attempts to play games, and searches.
Profile Information: This includes your description.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
Provide and maintain Trimry's functionalities.
Enhance user experience and improve the app.
Communicate with users about updates, promotions, or important notices.
Monitor and analyze usage patterns and trends.
4. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, certain user-generated content, such as questions, answers, and scores, may be visible to other Trimry users based on the app's functionalities and the privacy settings you choose.
5. Data Security
We employ a range of technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
6. User Rights
You have the right to:
Access the personal data we hold about you.
Rectify any inaccurate or incomplete data.
Request the deletion of your personal data.
Object to certain processing activities or withdraw consent previously given.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at support@trimry.com.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you through Trimry or via the email address associated with your account. Your continued use of Trimry after such changes will constitute your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.
8. Contact Us
For any questions, concerns, or requests related to this Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@trimry.com.